    "data": {
      "title": "Word Ladder Validity",
      "topics": [],
      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": false,
      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "// solver takes a string array and outputs a boolean\nvar solve = input =>\n    // check whether there are at least 2 inputs\n    !!input[1] &&\n    // check whether all inputs are the same length and whether all inputs are unique\n    input.every((o,i) => o.length == input[0].length && input.indexOf(o) == i) &&\n    // check whether adjacent words have exactly one letter difference\n    [...Array(input.length-1)].map((o,i) => \n        [...Array(input[i].length)].map((p,j) =>\n            input[i].charCodeAt(j) - input[i+1].charCodeAt(j)\n        )\n    ).every(o => o.filter(p => p).length == 1);\n\n// create string array and solve\nprint(solve([...Array(+readline())].map(o => readline())));\n",
      "statement": "A word ladder is a sequence of words of the same length where each word in the sequence changes exactly one letter in the previous word. Here's an example of a word ladder connecting \"mate\" and \"vial\":\n`\nmate\nmite\nmile\nmill\ndill\ndial\nvial\n`\nGiven the terms of an attempted word ladder, determine whether it is valid. That is, all the words should be the {{same length}}, and each step should result from changing exactly one letter. Also, there should be {{no duplicates}} among the words, and there should be {{at least 2 words}}.",
